    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nOn CRUX, we use this flow to compile a wheel:\n```\n/usr/bin/python3 -m build --wheel --skip-dependency-check --no-isolation\n/usr/bin/python3 -m installer --destdir=$PKG dist/*.whl\n```\n\nInstead of `cygdb`, `cython` and `cythonize`, we now get `cygbd3`, `cython3` and `cythonize3`. It turns out that reverting the latest [installer](https://pypi.org/project/installer/#history) update fixes that issue.\n\nI did have a look at the compiled wheels `entry_points.txt` and it correctly states the unversioned filenames:\n```\n❯ cat entry_points.txt\n[console_scripts]\ncygdb = Cython.Debugger.Cygdb:main\ncython = Cython.Compiler.Main:setuptools_main\ncythonize = Cython.Build.Cythonize:main\n```\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\n# example code\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\n_No response_\n\n### Python version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Cython version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
